The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Sunday, July 11, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	This year the Mohun Bagan Ratna award will be conferred posthumously on Gostho Pal, the legendary Indian defender of the pre-Independence era. Announcing this, the club secretary Anjan Mitra said the award will be presented to a family member of the player on July 29, which is observed as Mohun Bagan Day every year.				 																																																	Meanwhile, Brazilian Reggis Carlos Motero reached the city for a trial in Mohun Bagan. The six-foot striker from Sao Paulo, whose idol is Ronaldo, is expected to join practice under the supervision of coach Subrata Bhattacharya on Sunday. 				 																																																	 Nirmal Sangha-organised Jubilee Cup football tournament kicked off at Nababgunj, Isapore, on Saturday. Sixteen teams are participating in the meet, the final of which will be held on Sunday. 				 																																																	 Manoj Tewari of Kalighat Club has been named the CABs best player in the under-19 category. In the other junior categories, Arindam Ghosh and Amit Banerjee have jointly emerged best in the under-17 division while the under-15 award went to Chandan Pal, who has also been selected for the National Cricket Academy. 				 																																																	The CAB annual prize distribution function will be held on July 24. 				 																																																	 Indian Life Saving Society (ILSS) beat Calcutta Sports Association to emerge champions in the Ahiritola Youth Swimming Club-organised all Bengal Arnika Plus senior waterpolo meet at College Square on Saturday. In the final, ILLS won 7-5. 				 																																																	TABLE TENNIS: Inter-club team championship  Opening day action at Netaji Indoor Stadium from 10 am.
